description.space:
4 reasons to choose this apartment: 
1) The central position will allow you to walk everywhere in the historical center of Rome (Colosseo, Fori Imperiali, Quirinale, Trevi Fountain, ...) with no need of taxi or public transportation ( the metro Cavour stop is 1 minute walking and Termini Central Train Station is 10 minute walking away); 
2) The interior design comfortable, functional and elegant combining modern and antique; 
3) The services offered (daily cleaning,  A/C, smart TV with Netflix and many other ones) and the availability and courtesy of Salvatore (the host); 
4) Competitive prices compared to other accommodations with an equivalent offer.

The apartment is 480 sq feet, 1 floor above street level in a very quiet building of 17th century. It is divided into three spaces: living area with kitchen and sofa bed, bedroom, bathroom, small balcony. 
The apartment is brand new (end of restructuring in September 2016) and is equipped with every comfort. Air-conditioned, Wi-Fi, washing machine, dishwasher, smart TV with free Netflix. Kitchen with combined oven, electric espresso coffee. Bed with wooden base and a shower with vertical SPA system. 
The interior design was created by Dilber & Stolfi, the architectural firm that designed for Armani and Versace stores in New York and Bejiing. Through the creative genius of Davide Stolfi, the choice of excellent materials (Ariostea), handmade craftsman furniture (Furniture Bertini) together with  designer brands' furniture (Kartell Milano, Elica, Elleci, Foster), we have tried to transform the interior of the apartment into a manifesto of style, elegance and luxury “made in Italy”.
Last but not the least, during the refurbishment works of the apartments, we have discovered original walls from the 17th century and we have decided to preserve and restore them.
